<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1495] Allow TaskSequence to run for certain time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1495</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;To help the perf testing for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1483&quot; title=&quot;Change IndexSearcher multisegment searches to search each individual segment using a single HitCollector&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1483&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I added simple ability to specify a fixed run time (seconds) for a task sequence, eg:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;{ &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;XSearchWithSort&quot;&lt;/span&gt; SearchWithSort(doctitle:string) &amp;gt; : 2.7s
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;iterates on that subtask until 2.7 seconds have elapsed, and then sets the repetition count to how many iterations were done.  This is useful when you are running searches whose runtime may vary drastically.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
